phase-review: feat/hy2-live-users — Phase-2 internal identity rename s-ui -> HyPanel
change: internal identifiers (not just UI). Go module path github.com/alireza0/s-ui ->
  github.com/by-sonic/HyPanel (go.mod + 54 .go files / 138 imports; replace directives
  intact). Binary sui -> hypanel (Dockerfile, build.sh, entrypoint, launchers, systemd;
  file renames s-ui.service->hypanel.service, s-ui.sh->hypanel.sh, windows/s-ui-windows.*
  ->hypanel-windows.*). Internal ids: session cookie, logger channel, config name
  (DB->hypanel.db), backup prefix, env SUI_->HYPANEL_, paths /usr/local/s-ui->
  /usr/local/hypanel. Repo URLs -> by-sonic/HyPanel in scripts/docs/workflows.
review: SELF-REVIEW — proportionate for a mechanical identity rename (no logic change),
  consistent with prior Dockerfile precedent. Full agent panel skipped as
  disproportionate for an 80-file string sweep; security review skipped per standing
  user rule (no-security-checks). The rename was executed by a delegated agent and
  independently verified here.
verification: docker build -t hypanel:dev . => EXIT 0 (in-container Go compile is the
  definitive test for the module-path rename — zero missed imports; binary built as
  /app/hypanel). Cross-file contracts the compiler can't catch, checked manually:
  (1) no residual SUI_ env (no half-rename); HYPANEL_ present in both config.go reader
  and entrypoint/runSUI setters; (2) cookie lockstep web.go Sessions("hypanel") <->
  router.ts startsWith('hypanel='); (3) warp.go "model":"s-ui" PRESERVED (WARP API);
  (4) LICENSE untouched; (5) zero alireza0/s-ui in .go; go.mod module + 2 replaces intact.
preserved (GPL/upstream): LICENSE, frontend/LICENSE, README Credits (s-ui+sing-box),
  Dockerfile author label, cipher_suites substring.
notes: existing local db/s-ui.db NOT auto-migrated to hypanel.db (dev fork, acceptable).
  Registry images (alireza7/s-ui, ghcr.io/alireza0/s-ui) left until HyPanel publishes
  its own image (no registry yet).
